This war has made being RETROWATCHGUY a bit difficult. All I really want to do is photograph and post the bitchin’ vintage watches we all love. And I will continue to do just that. But, I cannot be silent while my people are fighting for our survival. Mourning the horrific deaths of the murdered. Praying that our friends’ kids and husbands bravely fighting this battle will be coming home. While being unable to comprehend that babies, children, and grandparents are held hostage deep within terror tunnels underneath Gaza. If that means I lose followers, that’s okay. We could never be friends in real life anyway. 

In solidarity with the brave men and women who are risking their lives at this moment to defend my country, I’m wearing this tough O&W Navichron, known for being a badass watch on the wrist of servicemen in the 1960’s. War isn’t new. It’s as old as time. We didn’t start this war, but we have no choice but to finish it.

With its super comfy semi-integrated bracelet, monocoque case, and 5 screw bezel, this Ebel has an unabashedly Gerald Genta essence. These still fly way low under the radar, but are all hiding and waiting for you to discover in the bottom of gramps underwear drawer
